{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Aeronaut Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Aeronaut Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = low gradient | location = [[Victoria Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|73|16|S|163|36|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|40|km|mi|abbr=on}} | width = | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Aviator Glacier]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Aeronaut Glacier''' ({{coord|73|16|S|163|36|E|type:glacier_region:AQ|display=inline,title}}) is a low gradient [[glacier]] extending {{convert|25|mi|adj=on}} draining northeast from [[Gair Mesa]] into the upper part of [[Aviator Glacier]] near [[Navigator Nunatak]], situated on the [[Borchgrevink Coast]], named for Anglo-Norwegian explorer [[Carsten Borchgrevink]] (1864-1934) in the western extremity of [[Victoria Land]], [[Antarctica]]. It was named by the northern party of [[New Zealand Geological Survey Antarctic Expedition]] of 1962&ndash;63 to commemorate the air support provided by [[U.S. Navy]] [[Squadron (aviation)|Squadron]] [[VX-6]], and in association with nearby Aviator Glacier.
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]]
