'''Seung Chan Kim ''' ({{ko-hhrm|김승찬}}; born April 15, 1991) is a [[South Korea]]n medical scientist and inventor. His main area of research is biomagnetism domestic core technology<sup>[''nonsensical translation'']</sup>. He received the 2009 [[Talent Award of Korea]] along with [[Yuna Kim]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yonsei.ac.kr/_custom/yonsei/_app/ocx/news/app.jsp?mode=view&ar_seq=12699&sr_volume=492&list_mode=list&sr_site=S&pager.offset=0|title=신지애·김승찬, '2009 대한민국 인재상' 수상|publisher=Yonsei University|accessdate=2016-09-19}}</ref> He serves as [[World Talent Exchange and Sharing Organization]] president.
==Career== Kim identified the cancer cell growth inhibition mechanism of magnetic-based [[cell division]] difference. Dispersed by the static [[magnetic field]], the core protein GCP3 in [[Spindle apparatus|spindle formation]], during cell division cycle, was identified for the first time in the world. This contributed to establish the scientific basis on the availability to the magnetic field for future anti-cancer therapy. From Harvard MGH research exchanges, the treatment of nerve cell to nerve cell turning the magnetic field grow into the direction perpendicular to the magnetic field that can be used in a certain direction based on research data.{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}} These properties provide a basis for cell regeneration. In particular, in the case of spinal cord and nerve disorders due to a mismatch between [[Synaptic vesicle|synaptic]] connections, it is crucial. It developed a first time patented technology uncovering a new era in medical science.<ref>{{cite journal|title=The application of magnets directs the orientation of neurite outgrowth in cultured human neuronal cells|first1=Seungchan|last1=Kim|first2=Woo-Seok|last2=Im|first3=Lami|last3=Kang|first4=Soon-Tae|last4=Lee|first5=Kon|last5=Chu|first6=Byoung In|last6=Kim|date=15 September 2008|publisher=|journal=J. Neurosci. Methods|volume=174|issue=1|pages=91–96|via=PubMed|doi=10.1016/j.jneumeth.2008.07.005|pmid=18682261}}</ref>
Currently he holds 163 intellectual patents. Various talent sharing donations and volunteering was made through creativity, science and decisive contribution. This applies as well as decisive contribution for strengthening humanity.<ref> {{cite news|url=http://news.dongascience.com/PHP/NewsView.php?kisaid=20130218100000000094&classcode=0110|title=과학도가 재능기부 전도사 된 사연은?|work=[[Dong-A Ilbo|Dong-A]] Science|accessdate=2016-09-19}}</ref>
Based on the Korea Talent Association ([[:ko:대한민국인재연합회|대한민국인재연합회]]), he established the World TESO ([[World Talent Exchange and Sharing Organization]]) in the [[Philippines]], [[Canada]], and [[Australia]]. He also has a major contribution to enhancing the international status of contributions to the scientific talent exchange, with the [[Republic of Korea]].{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}}
