'''''The Department of Mad Scientists: How DARPA is Remaking Our World''''', from the Internet to Artificial Limbs is a book by [[Michael Belfiore (author)|Michael Belfiore]] about the history and origins of [[DARPA]]. Belfiore describes DARPA's creation as the agency ARPA in [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]] and some of its notable contributions to artificial limbs, the Internet, space exploration and robotic automobiles.

Belfiore also highlights some of the unique aspects of DARPA's internal structure such as term limits for project managers, willingness to fund ambitious research, and subcontracting of all research.

